e computed (line 667)\n\n**Difference:**\n- `amount()` = this account's balance only (not including children)\n- `total()` = this account + all descendant accounts combined\n\n**Computation Timing:**\n- Computation is **lazy** – happens first time `amount()` or `total()` is called\n- Results are **cached** in `xdata_->self_details.total` and `xdata_->family_details.total`\n- Cache is **invalidated** when new postings are added (see `invalidate_xdata_cache()` at account.cc:121-142)\n\n---\n\n### 2. HOW BALANCE_T TRACKS ANNOTATED AMOUNTS\n\n**Location:** `src/balance.h` (lines 69-605)\n\n**Key Data Structure:**\n```cpp\nusing amounts_map = std::unordered_map<commodity_t*, amount_t>;\namounts_map amounts;\n```\n\nThis is an **unordered hash map** where:\n- **Key**: `commodity_t*` pointer (can point to either base commodities OR annotated commodities)\n- **Value**: `amount_t` object containing the quantity and commodity\n\n**How Annotated Commodities Appear:**\n\n1. **Each annotated lot is a SEPARATE entry** in the `amounts_map`\n   - Unannotated \"EUR\": might have key pointing to base commodity_t\n   - EUR with price annotation: has key pointing to `annotated_commodity_t` with that specific price\n   - EUR with different price: has key pointing to DIFFERENT `annotated_commodity_t`\n\n2. **Commodity Pointer Comparison:**\n   - Base commodities: `commodity_t*` points to single shared base object (e.g., \"EUR\")\n   - Annotated commodities: `commodity_t*` is subclass `annotated_commodity_t*` that wraps base + annotations\n   - Equality check (`commodity_t::operator==()`, commodity.h:146-150) compares pointer identity for base commodities, but handles annotated specially\n\n3. **Annotated Commodity Definition** (annotate.h:135-190):\n```cpp\nclass annotated_commodity_t : public commodity_t {\n  commodity_t* ptr;              // Points to base commodity\n  annotation_t details;          // Contains price, date, tag, value_expr\n};\n```\n\n**Where Annotations Live:**\n- **Price**: `details.price` – optional amount_t\n- **Date**: `details.date` – optional date_t (lot acquisition date)\n- **Tag**: `details.tag` – optional string (user-defined identifier)\n- **Value Expression**: `details.value_expr` – optional expr_t\n\n---\n\n### 3. HOW POSTINGS AFFECT ACCOUNT BALANCES\n\n**Location:** `src/account.cc:144-150`, `src/xact.cc:548-584`\n\n**When a posting is added:**\n\n1. **`post_t::account->add_post(post)`** is called (account.cc:144-150)\n   - Simply appends posting to `posts` list: `posts.push_back(post)` (line 145)\n   - **Invalidates xdata cache** by calling `invalidate_xdata_cache(this)` (line 149)\n   - Sets `xdata_.self_details.gathered = false` and `calculated = false`\n   - Also invalidates parent accounts up the hierarchy (lines 131-140)\n\n2. **Balance is NOT updated eagerly** – posting is just added to the list\n\n3. **Balance is computed lazily** when `amount()` or `total()` is called next\n\n**Flow in Transaction Finalization** (xact.cc:548-584):\n\n1. `xact_base_t::finalize()` completes transaction balancing (lines 150-584)\n2. **At line 568**: `post->account->add_post(post)` – adds post to account\n3. **At line 571-572**: Sets flags:\n   ```cpp\n   post->xdata().add_flags(POST_EXT_VISITED);\n   post->account->xdata().add_flags(ACCOUNT_EXT_VISITED);\n   ```\n4. These flags enable `amount()` to include the posting in balance calculations\n\n---\n\n### 4. ARE ACCOUNT BALANCES AVAILABLE DURING FINALIZE()?\n\n**Location:** `src/xact.cc:150-584`\n\n**YES, but with caveats:**\n\n1. **During finalize(), posts are NOT yet added to accounts** (until line 548-584)\n   - Balance calculation happens in lines 150-546\n   - Posts are only added to accounts at lines 548-584\n\n2. **At line 568 when `add_post()` is called**, the posting becomes accessible via `account->posts`\n   - However, the balance is NOT automatically recalculated\n   - Need to call `account->amount()` or `account->total()` to recompute\n\n3. **Critical:** Lines 332-346 show automatic FIFO/LIFO lot matching:\n   ```cpp\n   if (journal && journal->lot_matching_policy != \"\" && journal->lot_matching_policy != \"none\") {\n     for (post_t* post : copy) {\n       if (post->amount.sign() < 0 && !post->amount.has_annotation() && !post->cost) {\n         if (std::optional<amount_t> matched =\n               commodity_pool_t::current_pool->match_lot(...)) {\n           post->amount = *matched;  // Annotate with matched lot\n         }\n       }\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n   - This happens BEFORE posts are added to accounts (line 348 is inside the loop)\n   - `match_lot()` operates on **global commodity_pool's lots**, not account balances\n\n4. **Why?** The pool tracks all lots seen across the entire journal, so it can match sales against accumulated purchases\n\n---\n\n### 5. ACCOUNT HIERARCHY AND BALANCE AGGREGATION\n\n**Location:** `src/account.h:55-239`, `src/account.cc:665-703`\n\n**Hierarchy Structure:**\n```cpp\naccount_t* parent;                    // Parent account pointer (nullptr for root)\naccounts_map accounts;                // Children indexed by name\n```\n\n**Balance Aggregation:**\n- **`amount()`** = self account only\n- **`total()`** = self + ALL descendants recursively\n\n**self_details() vs family_details()**:\n- `self_details()` (account.cc:683-691): Only this account's postings\n- `family_details()` (account.cc:693-703): This account + all children's family details\n  - Iterates children: `xdata_->family_details += pair.second->family_details()`\n  - Then adds self: `xdata_->family_details += self_details()`\n\n**Parent accounts automatically aggregate** because `total()` sums children recursively\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY DATA STRUCTURES AND COMMODITY COMPARISON\n\n**amounts_map in balance_t** (balance.h:99):\n```cpp\nusing amounts_map = std::unordered_map<commodity_t*, amount_t>;\n```\n\n**How Commodity Comparison Works:**\n\n1. **Base Commodities:** \n   - Hash key is `commodity_t*` pointer\n   - Same base commodity always uses same pointer\n   - All \"EUR\" postings share one entry (unless annotated)\n\n2. **Annotated Commodities:**\n   - Each unique annotation gets a NEW `annotated_commodity_t` instance\n   - \"EUR {1.32}\" gets one annotated_commodity_t\n   - \"EUR {1.33}\" gets a DIFFERENT annotated_commodity_t\n   - Each has its own entry in the amounts_map\n\n3. **Equality** (commodity.h:146-150):\n   ```cpp\n   virtual bool operator==(const commodity_t& comm) const {\n     if (comm.annotated)\n       return comm == *this;\n     return base.get() == comm.base.get();\n   }\n   ```\n   - Compares base pointers for unannotated\n   - Recursively compares for annotated\n\n4. **Pool Management** (pool.h:68-72):\n   ```cpp\n   annotated_commodities_map =\n       std::map<std::pair<string, annotation_t>, std::shared_ptr<annotated_commodity_t>>;\n   annotated_commodities_map annotated_commodities;\n   ```\n   - Pool caches annotated commodities by (symbol, annotation_t) pair\n   - Ensures same annotation gets same annotated_commodity_t instance\n\n---\n\n### 7. BALANCE_T SORT ORDER (NEW FEATURE)\n\n**Location:** `src/balance.h:102-105`\n\n```cpp\nenum class lot_sort_order : std::uint8_t { by_commodity, fifo, lifo };\nlot_sort_order sort_order = lot_sort_order::by_commodity;\n```\n\n- Stores which order to display/process lots\n- Used with new helper functions (balance.h:600-602):\n  - `average_lot_prices()`\n  - `fifo_lot_prices()`\n  - `lifo_lot_prices()`\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY TABLE: Balance Computation\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Storage Location** | `account_t::posts` list + `xdata_t::self_details.total` cache |\n| **Computation** | Lazy – on-demand when `amount()`/`total()` called |\n| **Caching** | Yes – `xdata_->self_details.total` and `xdata_->family_details.total` |\n| **Cache Invalidation** | When `add_post()` called – invalidates self and ancestors |\n| **Annotated Lots** | Separate `amounts_map` entries per unique annotation |\n| **Lot Key Type** | `commodity_t*` (pointer to base or annotated commodity) |\n| **Parent Aggregation** | Recursive – `total()` sums all descendants |\n| **During finalize()** | Posts added to accounts at lines 548-584; balances still lazy |\n| **Lot Matching** | Operates on pool's global lots via `match_lot()`, not account balance |\n\n---\n\n### CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS FOR ISSUE #164\n\n**New Fields Added:**\n1. **journal.h**: `lot_matching_policy` field (journal.cc:11)\n2. **post.h**: `POST_AMOUNT_USER_ANNOTATED` and `POST_AMOUNT_USER_DATE` flags (post.h:63-64)\n3. **pool.h**: `match_lot()` function (pool.h:115-116)\n4. **balance.h**: `lot_sort_order` enum (balance.h:102)\n\n**Key Insight:** FIFO/LIFO matching operates **during finalize()** at lines 332-346, BEFORE posts are added to accounts. It matches against the commodity pool's global lot history, not individual account balances.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>81154</total_tokens><tool_uses>29</tool_uses><duration_ms>71222</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-johnw-src-ledger-fix-164/tasks/a5df3d08c0017054d.output",
